
Installing Mondrian:

The program (mondrian) should be placed in a directory that is on your
execution path.  /usr/bin or ~/bin are usually good choices.


Running Mondrian:

If the program crashes or if you find other bugs, please check the web page
first to see if they have already been reported.

On OS X, this program requires XQuartz, the X11 server.  Before running
this program, you must first start XQuartz.


Notes on Mondrian:

mondrian creates window layouts for use with JX.  The on-line help explains
all the features of the program.

The main web page for JX is

    http://github.com/jx_application_framework/

